article.headline: Arkansas St. 108, Central Baptist 71
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Jeremy Thomas scored 23 points on 7-of-7 shooting to lead Arkansas State over Central Baptist 108-71 Thursday night. Daniel Bryant, Eric McKinney and Mike Lance scored 14 points each for the Red Wolves (6-1). Central Baptist (7-6) shot 13-of-27 from 3-point range, but the Mustangs were blown out. They trailed 63-43 at halftime. Arkansas State outrebounded Central Baptist 45-26. Thomas contributed 10 rebounds. Arkansas State had 23 assists and only 12 turnovers. Eleven Red Wolves played at least 10 minutes.
